items.title: From Sex Appeal to the Far Right, Brigitte Bardot Symbolized a Changing France
items.description: In the decades after becoming a megastar, the French actress became as known for her politics as she once had been for her acting career.

items.title: Brigitte Bardot, French Movie Icon Who Renounced Stardom, Dies at 91
items.description: “And God Created Woman” made her a world-famous sex symbol in the 1950s. She later gave up acting to devote her life to animal welfare.
